results.name: The sequence S = a(1), a(2), ... is defined by a(1)=1, if d,e,f are consecutive digits then we do not have d > e < f, and S is always extended with the smallest integer not yet present in S.
reference: Eric Angelini, Posting to Sequence Fans Mailing List, Sep 28 2013
